# What is Ansible

### What is Ansible?

- Answerable -> Ansible
- Ansible is an open-source automation tool
- You can use Ansible to manage on or many computers at once
- Can do tasks like configuration management, application deployment, infrastructure setup, etc.
- The details about the resources to manage hosts are kept in a file called Ansible inventory
- The instructions to run on hosts are kept in YAML files  called Playbooks
- When the playbook is run, a connection is made to the host systems and playbook instructions are executed on the hosts
